Moments after winning the Dusi Canoe Marathon paddler Andy Birkett just wanted to quench his thirst after a scorching day on the river. The mercury reached 37 degrees on Wednesday which along with low river levels because of the drought made for a tough day on the water.Birkett who led the race from start to finish won in a time of just over 8 hours 32 minutes. He said he was delighted to overcome the conditions and take the victory.He beat closest rival Sibonelo Kwela by nearly 24 minutes in a dominant display. Kwela was aiming to become the first even black paddler to win the K1 solo race having previously won the K2 pairs category.TMG Digital/TimesLIVE